text.section:
The payment or tender of a written offer required by subsection (e) or (f) of this section must be accompanied by the following:
A statement of partnership assets and liabilities as of the date of dissociation;
The latest available partnership balance sheet and income statement, if any;
An explanation of how the estimated amount of the payment was calculated; and
Written notice that unless the dissociated partner commences an action to determine the buyout price, any offsets under subsection (c) of this section, or other terms of the obligation to purchase within 120 days after the written notice, the payment is in full satisfaction of the obligation to purchase.
